item.description:
It's a template that you can build up your own requests grouped in folders. This level should define your own test user accounts that per environment.

# Specify Your Secret

In Pre-request Script section, you should specify secret that is defined in postman Globals variable

<img src="https://content.pstmn.io/b86ca1ae-acc3-4f63-98a0-5f92ed2cc935/aW1hZ2UucG5n" width="613" height="265">

``` javascript
// Please deine your secret in global variables with naming convetion: secret_app-account-id
const password = pm.globals.get('${YOUR_SECRET_VAR_DEFINED_IN_GLOBALS}');
// e.g.
const password = pm.globals.get('secret_auto');

 ```

# Environment Data

Some values such as `region` and `client_id` may vary per environment so you can set up these configurations on your folder.

The configurations that are allowed to configure on environment level are:

- region
- client_id
- password


``` javascript
const env_data = {
    dev: {
        region: 'us-east-1',
        client_id: 'YOUR_CLIENT_ID',
        password: password,
    },
    qa: {
        region: 'us-east-1',
        client_id: 'YOUR_CLIENT_ID',
        password: password,
    },
    demo: {
        region: 'us-west-2',
        client_id: 'YOUR_CLIENT_ID',
        password: password,
    },
    prod: {
        region: 'us-west-2',
        client_id: 'YOUR_CLIENT_ID',
        password: password,
    }
}

 ```

Note: we can consider move these configurations to postman enveironments variables instead. (TBD)

